\b Discussion and limitations (Part 2)\b0\par
The derived gate charge depends on the accuracy of the gate-resistor voltage measurement and on the chosen integration window. High-side measurements are especially susceptible to common-mode interference due to the rapidly moving reference potential. In addition, probe capacitance (approximately 1 pF) can introduce displacement currents under high dV/dt conditions, which can bias the apparent gate current and thus the integrated charge. These effects are documented and considered when comparing Qg values across operating points and device types.\par

